  "doc_id": "59377",
  "text": "The simulation of the dynamic response in localised blast-loaded FMLs is of importance owing to the differences between the response modes to this type of loading and global blasts. The apparently peculiar nature of this kind of loads renders the dynamic solution, damage pattern, thresholds and critical conditions intrinsically different. When localised blast loads are applied to plates, it is normal practice to idealise the localised blast as pressure loading relating to impulse obtained from actual experiment. For localised blast at the centre of a plate, the pressure loading is a function of time and distance from the centre of the plate [CITATION_1] .",
